DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.7.3.231
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 231
EP  - 237
VL  - 7
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Intelligent problem-solving, whether by man or by machine, implies selective rather than just rapid behavior. Humans achieve this selectivity through heuristics?principles that, on the average, contribute to reduction of search in problem-solving. Heuristic programming is the construction of computer problem-solving programs whose behavior is similarly organized. This paper surveys the present and potential use of heuristic programming in management science.
